{{Quote|He was hunting shoal darters [...] Trying to make a connection—any connection [...] He doesn't know anything.|[[Vilim Disra]]|<ref name="Specter of the Past">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>}}
'''Shoal darters''' were creatures that some people hunted. The phrase "hunting shoal darters" meant to extensively search for something that may not be there.<ref name="Specter of the Past" />

==Behind the scenes==
The expression "hunting shoal darters" is used to convey the same meaning as going on a "wild goose chase."

